description: The Virtue of Nationalism, now referred to as “the book that launched a movement,” was updated by Jewish political philosopher Yoram Hazony and rereleased this summer. author: Jason E. Thompson
description: America feels broken, from our conversations to our communities to our politics. Charlie Kirk‘s assassination was a tragic reminder of just how fragile our civic life has become. Regardless of political views, his death crossed a line that must never be crossed. Violence is not debate, protest, or even dissent. It’s the rejection of democracy, […]
